comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:58:35.029Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: context-engine items define relevance assembly and evaluation but no dedicated typed-graph analytics portfolio covering project planning,impact,community,and incremental temporal algorithms; this item supplies those graph primitives without duplicating ranking policy."
  "2026-07-14T09:43:36.815Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: deliver the first exact deterministic analytics tranche over registered relationship semantics, including execution-order and impact/knowledge signals with provenance rather than opaque scores."
  "2026-07-14T10:19:33.632Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: added exact deterministic ordering analytics with Kahn layers, frontier, depth, topological order, critical path, and SCC cycle reporting; bounded impact with shortest explanation paths; weak/strong knowledge components, orphans, hubs; and temporal snapshot comparison. Associative relationships are excluded from execution blockers through registry precedence rather than hard-coded kind names."
  "2026-07-14T10:48:29.881Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 1 evidence: longest-path analysis now explicitly excludes cyclic targets reached from the acyclic prefix, and temporal comparison recursively stabilizes complete edge/payload key ordering. Cycle-entry and nested payload-order regressions pass; full repository coverage is exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T11:06:16.985Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 2 evidence: stable temporal keys now honor runtime objects with custom toJSON semantics before recursive key sorting. Equivalent Date and ISO payload values compare unchanged without altering native undefined omission behavior."
  "2026-07-14T11:19:54.468Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 3 evidence: documented the deliberate source-before-target fallback as compatibility behavior for legacy and JSON-parsed relationship definitions; focused SDK tests, lint, duplicate detection, CodeFactor rules, and typecheck pass."
  "2026-07-14T11:44:56.773Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 4 evidence: impact analysis now performs one BFS with parent-map path reconstruction instead of one shortest-path traversal per affected node. Regression coverage proves bounded and cyclic semantics and zero shortestPath calls; installed-package 10,000-node fan-out visited 10,001 nodes once in 27.28 ms. Full coverage is exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,681 tests."
  "2026-07-17T19:21:59.493Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress: execution/knowledge/impact analytics are now operable from the workspace surface via pm graph analyze and pm graph impact (CLI + pm_graph MCP + PmClient.graph). analyze returns node/edge counts plus execution (acyclic, topological layers, prerequisite frontier, critical path, genuine ordering cycles) and knowledge (components, orphans, degree hubs) summaries with a shared bounded sample limit; impact returns discovery-ordered affected rows with distance and an explaining path, honoring direction/kind/depth/limit bounds and truncation metadata. Regression spec exercises both envelopes, summary suppression, and bound enforcement on a live temp workspace."
  "2026-07-17T20:19:41.275Z",maintainer-agent,"Analytics tranche verification (commit a3b47c97): detectRelationshipCommunities, findRedundantRelationshipEdges, and computeRelationshipDominators shipped with exact 100/100/100/100 coverage inside the 5,842-test full gate. Live-workspace sanity: communities converged in 5 sweeps over ~3.1k edges (149 clusters, largest 134), redundancy surfaced real blocked_by/blocks shortcut triples with witnesses, dominators over pm-usfg ranked pm-8a2s as the 91-item gate. Remaining canonical scope on this feature: incremental cached analytics only."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:19:36.348Z",codex-gpt5,"Remaining canonical scope after this PR: dominators, community algorithms beyond exact components, redundancy detection, incremental cached analytics, and CLI/MCP projections; keep feature open."
  "2026-07-17T20:01:05.109Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress (graph-query-surface lane, 2026-07-17): three of this feature's recorded remaining-scope analytics shipped as public SDK primitives in new src/sdk/graph/analytics.ts — detectRelationshipCommunities (deterministic asynchronous label propagation, sorted sweeps, lexicographic tie-break, maxIterations/minSize bounds, convergence reporting), findRedundantRelationshipEdges (transitive-reduction scan joining each directed ordering/hierarchy kind with its inverse spelling in semantic orientation, per-edge bounded BFS witness paths), computeRelationshipDominators (Cooper-Harvey-Kennedy immediate dominators over the root's reachable subgraph with per-node gating weights). Exposed as pm graph communities/redundancy/dominators + pm_graph MCP + PmClient.graph with counts-first envelopes, sample bounds, and cost metadata. Remaining canonical scope: incremental cached analytics only (dominators/communities/redundancy now shipped)."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:02:21.487Z",codex-gpt5,Execution analytics need an explicit precedence direction in each ordering-kind definition. An ordering boolean alone cannot distinguish source-blocks-target from source-blocked-by-target without guessing from labels.
